about.summary: Docker container for running PyTorch scripts to train and host PyTorch models on SageMaker.

name: sagemaker-pytorch-container
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "sagemaker-pytorch-container" %}
{% set version = "1.0.9" %}

package:
  name: "{{ name|lower }}"
  version: "{{ version }}"

source:
  url: "https://github.com/aws/{{ name }}/archive/v{{ version }}.tar.gz"
  sha256: f211f32ccc299714d3e6a386e7f7dbea71033d82246ad45055ea7da966f57721

build:
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"
  noarch: python

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python >=2.7,<3.7
  run:
    - python >=2.7,<3.7
    - numpy >=1.16.4
    - pillow >=6.2.0
    - retrying >=1.3.3
    - sagemaker_containers
    - six >=1.12.0
    - pytorch-cpu
test:
  imports:
    - sagemaker_pytorch_container

about:
  home: "https://github.com/aws/sagemaker-pytorch-container/"
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_family: APACHE
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: "Docker container for running PyTorch scripts to train and host PyTorch models on SageMaker."
  doc_url: https://sagemaker.readthedocs.io/en/stable/using_pytorch.html
  dev_url: https://github.com/aws/sagemaker-pytorch-container/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - rluria14
    - benhuff
    - oblute
